22:34.000 --> 22:39.000
That was until a student of both Thompson and Rutherford came along to enlighten the world.

22:39.000 --> 22:45.000
A Danish physicist called Niels Bohr published a brand new model for the atom in 1913.

22:46.000 --> 22:48.000
Now, to give some background on Bohr's paper,

22:48.000 --> 22:52.000
over the last few years, scientists like Max Planck and Albert Einstein

22:52.000 --> 22:57.000
