25:52.000 --> 26:02.000
Returning to the nucleus, at this point there was still not much known about it, other than the fact that it was very small compared to the size of the atom and that it was positively charged.

26:02.000 --> 26:09.000
In the same year that Bohr published his atomic model, an English chemist called Frederick Soddy and a Polish chemist called Kazimierz Fajans,

26:09.000 --> 26:17.000
