32:40.000 --> 32:43.000
This means that even you and I have wavelengths of our own.

32:43.000 --> 32:48.000
The thing is though, according to this equation, the bigger the mass, the smaller the wavelength.

32:48.000 --> 32:51.000
So the wavelength of a person is completely negligible.

32:51.000 --> 32:56.000
However, an electron is so tiny that its wavelength becomes significant.

32:56.000 --> 33:01.000
So not only can it behave as a particle, it can behave as a wave.

33:01.000 --> 33:08.000
This was proved experimentally a few years later by two separate groups who independently performed very similar experiments.

33:08.000 --> 33:15.000
One group was led by the English physicist George Padgett Thompson, the son of Joseph John Thompson who discovered the electron.

33:15.000 --> 33:19.000
The other group was led by the American physicist Clinton Davison.

33:19.000 --> 33:29.000
